This turn of the tide no way pleas'd the Roman Catholicks. At 
                  Ʋtrecht and in ſeveral other places, they were in hopes that the French would return; and that then they ſhould be put into poſſeſſion of the Government of the Province;

 nay they gave it out ſo in publick. They were ſo obſtinate at Otmarſum, that they would not ſurrender their Churches to thoſe of the Reformed Religion, which caus'd ſome diſorders at firſt, though they were quickly appeas'd.
